<br>
I started me warrior out of boredom and it wasnt a serious character until I actually tried tanking with a group. I was on the edge of my seat, biting me lip, and would not dare for even a second think about running to the fridge real quick.<br>
<br>
Although I DID like being a warrior, I wasnt completly hooked untill Lord Nagafen.<br>
<br>
I remember looking around, asking who the MT was, and having EVERYONE stare at me.<br>
<br>
I remember charging and watching Nagafen scaling getting bigger and bigger as I got closer. I remember having to pan straight up just to see a portion of his neck.<br>
<br>
NEVER in me time playing EQ did me knuckles go white, me face go pale, and a wave of nervousness and nasuea flow over me. I would later discover this new alien sensation was a mixture of terror, adreniline, excitement, and pure awe after the battle as I looked down at the Lord of Lavastorm and thought to myself &quot;Wow! I just tanked that!&quot;<br>
<br>
Me enchanter was retired that day.<br>
It simply could not compete with that sensation.<br>
And I get that sensation with each new mob.<br>
Lady Vox, Trak, Gorenaire, Vindi (I actually got sick when facing him *LOL*)<br>
<br>
Seriously, what other class can really compare with that?<br>
<br>
